article.description: Bialkowski, Kurfis lead Lehigh past Columbia 24-10
article.headline: Bialkowski, Kurfis lead Lehigh past Columbia 24-10
article.linkText: Bialkowski, Kurfis lead Lehigh past Columbia 24-10
article.story: NEW YORK -- Brandon Bialkowski threw for 320 yards and three touchdowns to lead Lehigh to a 24-10 win over Columbia on Saturday. Two of Bialkowski's touchdown passes were caught by Lee Kurfis, who finished with 14 receptions for 130 yards. His 14 catches tied the school's single-game record. Lehigh (5-1) took a 17-3 lead in the second quarter with a pair Bialkowski touchdown passes, the first being a 6-yarder to Tyler Coyle. A little over two minutes later Kurfis hauled in a 10-yarder for a score. Marcorus Garrett cut the Lehigh lead to 17-10 late in the third with a 12-yard touchdown run for Columbia (0-4). Bialkowski then connected with Kurfis for an 8-yard score early in the fourth to extend the Mountain Hawks' lead to 24-10. Garrett finished with 27 carries for 150 yards, but the Lions couldn't get anything going in passing game, where they managed a total of just 71 yards.
